h3. Ingredients

* 2 bunches arugula (rocket)
* 5-6 Tablespoon vinaigrette (or just 2 Tablespoon balsamic vinegar + 4 Tablespoon olive oil)
* salt
* pepper
* ¼ cup parmesan cheese, thinly sliced or coarsely grated
* ¼ cup toasted pine nuts

h3. Method

Wash and thoroughly dry arugula, then place in bowl. Toss with vinaigrette,
salt, and pepper, and transfer to salad plates.

Top with cheese and nuts.

h3. Notes

Toss the pine nuts with a tiny amount of oil and toast in a frying pan over
medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until golden brown. If the pan starts to
smoke, turn down the heat.
